HeidelbergCement to Open 200-Million-Euro Kazakh Plant in 2013

-- B y   N a r i m a n   G i z i t d i n o v
-- 
2011-06-27T11:27:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-27/heidelbergcement-to-open-200-million-euro-kazakh-plant-in-2013.html
HeidelbergCement AG (HEI) , the German
cement maker owned by billionaire Ludwig Merckle, plans to start
production at a 200-million-euro ($283 million) cement plant in
 Kazakhstan  in 2013, the Central Asian nationâ€™s Industry Ministry
said.  HeidelbergCement has invested 70 million euros in
infrastructure around the plant, which will produce 1 million
tons of cement a year, board member Andreas Kern told Deputy
Prime Minister Aset Isekeshev during a meeting today, the
Astana-based ministry said by e-mail. The plant, which is
located in the western region of Mangistau, may double capacity
in the future, it added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
